      "text": [
        ": قُلْتُ لَهُ مَا حَدُّ آكِلِ اَلرِّبَا بَعْدَ اَلْبَيِّنَةِ قَالَ \"يُؤَدَّبُ فَإِنْ عَادَ أُدِّبَ فَإِنْ عَادَ قُتِلَ\"."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
          "Hadith.5132 - Ishaq ibn Ammar and Samaah narrated from Abu Basir from Abu Abdullah (as) who said: I asked Imam - \"What is the punishment for one who consumes usury after clear evidence (has been established)?\"\nImam (as) replied: \"He is to be disciplined. If he returns to it, he is disciplined again. If he repeats it a third time, he is to be killed.\""
        ]
      }
    },
